@ var nameOfTheVariable = [1, 3.5, "Gustavo", True, ...];

or 

@ var nameOfTheVariable = new Array(element1, element2, ...);

//The array can store any type of value, including other arrays or objects.

arrayName.length //this is a property that returns the length of the array (this will start by 1, different than the array index).



Example:

var array1 = ['Gustavo', 18]
array1[0];
>>> 'Gustavo'
array1.length;
>>> 2
